  <scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_c27f7e80b18bedc389deab63a10119e7">
    <head>Scope and content</head>
<p>Photographs of Daisy Farrand's garden at the Andrew Dickson White House, Cornell University include eight photographs by Margaret Bourke-White and six original prints, three modern prints, two modern negatives of photographs by John Troy; includes photographs before and after renovation. n. Also, recollections of Daisy Farrand by Elizabeth Wells and Kay Butterfield.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <prefercite audience="internal" id="aspace_e62eab9397892a7059280f00b350b17e">
    <head>Preferred Citation</head>
<p>Margaret Carleton Farrand miscellany, #3275. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
  <bioghist audience="internal" id="aspace_9107e4cdbeff040315a262984b2f2c70">
    <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
<p>Margaret (Daisy) Farrand was the wife of Cornell University president Livingston Farrand. The "Secret Garden" is in back of the Andrew Dickson White House on the Cornell campus.</p>  </bioghist>
